Dissecting IPv6


IPv4 - Uses a 32-bit address represented by dotted decimal notation

IPv6 - Uses a 128-bit address represented using hexadecimal notation



IPv6 Features - 
Stateful and stateless autoconfiguration
No broadcast, uses multicast
Optional extension headers
  Fragmentation or IP Security



IPv6 Requires ICMPv6

Network Layer in version 4 - IGMP,ICMP,IPv4,ARP
Network Layer in version 6 - ICMPv6, IPv6 (IGMP and ARP not necessary)


